Fear-stricken actress Motsoaledi Setumo has fled her parental home in Kagiso, on the West Rand, after suspecting that her enemies were conjuring up an evil spirit or casting a bad spell on her. Motsoaledi, who plays Mmabatho on Mzansi Magic's popular soapie The Queen, is now renting an apartment in Fourways, north of Joburg. The sultry actress, who also played Thabitha Cele on Generations: The Legacy, bolted from her Krugersdorp home after discovering that her brand-new BMW 1 series and the garage in which she had parked it were sprinkled with what resembled blood. TO READ THE FULL STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD AT YOUR NEAREST STORE